scene.message:
Kandori: Heh...{nl}
So even I can be defeated...{nl}
You were right, Nanjo.{waitkey}{clearbox}I... could only ever{nl}
live this way.{waitkey}{clearbox}Perhaps I invited you here{nl}
because I wanted to hear{nl}
someone say that...{waitkey}Heh... Pathetic, and yet{nl}
it feels good...{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: So you've seen{nl}
through the riddle of the{nl}
two worlds as well...{waitkey}Impressive.{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: It means that you,{nl}
and the world you came{nl}
from, are nothing but{waitkey}the figment of a certain{nl}
person's imagination,{nl}
Maki Sonomura...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: ...You are most likely{nl}
the ideal self of the{nl}
Maki Sonomura we know.{waitkey}{clearbox}And that town where you{nl}
live is the world inside{nl}
Maki Sonomura's heart...{waitkey}Isn't that right, Kandori?{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Exactly...{nl}
Not just you. Mai and Aki{nl}
too are shadows within{waitkey}Maki Sonomura's heart...{nl}
mere reflections of her.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: MAKI.{nl}
MAI, AKI...{nl}
A simple rearrangement{nl}
of the letters.{waitkey}{clearbox}Sonomura must have imagined{nl}
a paradise all her own,{nl}
deep within her heart...{waitkey}{clearbox}Modeled on the town as it{nl}
was right up until she was{nl}
hospitalized...{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: That's nuts...{nl}
So the police station being{nl}
gone, and the hospital{waitkey}turning into a castle{nl}
and all that...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Because a paradise{nl}
has no need of them...{nl}
Only what suits oneself{waitkey}need exist. Anyone would{nl}
think that way.{waitkey}{clearbox}Kozai and Naito being summoned{nl}
must also be Sonomura's{nl}
unconscious wish.{waitkey}The boy she admired and her{nl}
best friend - those alone{nl}
she wanted to be real...{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: It was a month ago{nl}
that the Deva System's{nl}
startup test succeeded.{waitkey}{clearbox}But... even before that,{nl}
she and the system were{nl}
linked.{waitkey}{clearbox}Her wavelength and the{nl}
system's must have synced{nl}
on a spiritual level...{waitkey}{clearbox}Fused with the power to{nl}
affect dimensions, her inner{nl}
paradise became something{nl}
beyond imagination...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: And then you made{nl}
contact with Mai, the{nl}
keeper of that paradise...{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Mai... no,{nl}
that Maki was lonely...{waitkey}{clearbox}Her role was to provide{nl}
the ideal Maki - you -{nl}
a world that suited you,{waitkey}as comfort for the real{nl}
Maki. The rest you{nl}
already know...{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Then go and meet{nl}
your true self...{nl}
She is here within{waitkey}this castle...{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: I am me!{nl}
That's... that's just{nl}
too cruel!{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: You're not going after{nl}
her? You're the only one{nl}
who can save her.{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Maki Sonomura...{nl}
must come to know her own{nl}
true heart. If she doesn't,{waitkey}she'll repeat my mistake...{waitkey}{clearbox}Go to her...{wait_fr:88} The same{nl}
road I walked...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: I'd been thinking{nl}
about it all along.{nl}
When I reached the answer,{waitkey}even I was shaken, though.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: ...{wait_fr:88}I finally killed{nl}
the bastard, and yet...{wait_fr:88}{nl}
What is this emptiness...{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Are you serious...{nl}
What's going to happen{nl}
to Maki?{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: I can't believe it...{nl}
What happens to Sonomura?{nl}
Hey?!{waitkey}{ret}

'The life of man is fifty{nl}
years. Set against the lowest{nl}
heaven, it is but{waitkey}a fleeting dream.'{nl}
So it is written...{waitkey}{ret}
